WHILE medicine can deliver amazing results they only work if people take them as prescribed. People are warned against not following directions such as taking the wrong dose, not finishing a prescribed course and not following the doctor or pharmacist’s instructions. These mistakes limit the effectiveness of the treatment, set back your treatment or make your problems worse! Dr Nicola Lister, chief scientific officer and medical director of Novartis Southern Africa, said: “Medicines are carefully researched and formulated chemicals, and in order for them to be effective, they have to be taken as directed.” So, what to do? 